\lambda
\mu(x):=\frac{1}{x}\lambda(x)
\mu
 \mu([0,1])=\int 1_{[0,1]}\, d\mu=\int_{[0,1]}\frac{1}{x}\, d\lambda(x). 
\infty
\mu ([0,1])\geq \mu \left(\bigcup_{n=1}^{\infty} \left[\frac{1}{n} ,1\right]\right) =\lim_{n\to\infty} \mu \left( \left[\frac{1}{n} ,1\right]\right) =\lim_{n\to\infty} \int_{\frac{1}{n} }^{1} \frac{1}{x} d\lambda (x) =\lim_{n\to\infty} \ln n =\infty 
